  <description type="morphology">Leaves: petiole 2–4 mm, sparsely hairy; blade broadly oblanceolate to obovate, 2–8 × 1–3 cm, length 2–3 times width, membranous, base cuneate to rounded, margins coarsely serrate, apex acute to obtuse. Panicles open, pyramidal, 5–20 × 3–10 cm. Pedicels 2–3 mm. Flowers 3–5 mm diam.; hypanthia abaxial surface glabrous or glabrate; sepals 0.8–1.5 mm; petals 1.3–1.5(–3) mm; stamens 30–35, 2 times petal length. 2n = 36, 54.</description>
